b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe29114.htm)  [Next](sbe29116.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1421228750/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n_The Grihya Sutras, Part 1 (SBE29)_ , by Hermann Oldenberg, [1886], at sacred-\ntexts.com\n\n* * *\n\n### KA _N_ _D_ IK\xc3\x82 16.\n\n1 1. In the sixth month the Annapra _s_ ana (i.e. the first feeding with solid\nfood).\n\n2\\. Goat's flesh, if he is desirous of nourishment,\n\n3\\. Flesh of partridge, if desirous of holy lustre,\n\n4\\. Boiled rice with ghee, if desirous of splendour:\n\n5\\. (Such) food, mixed with curds, honey and ghee he should give (to the\nchild) to eat with (the verse), 'Lord of food, give us food painless and\nstrong;\n\np. 184\n\nbring forward the giver; bestow power on us, on men and animals.'\n\n6\\. The rite only (without the Mantra) for a girl.\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[183:1](sbe29115.htm#fr_444) 16, 1 seq. Comp. Sa\xe1\xb9\x85kh.-G _ri_ hya I, 27, 1 seq.\nThe two texts are nearly word for word identical.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: I, 17](sbe29116.htm)\n\n"